f=Engineering/quinn/custom/test-strategy/SKILL.md · in=test-strategy quinn's quality law: test pyramid (what kinds tests, what proportion), coverage floors, release-gate matrix (which test tiers change type pass before ship). "quinn's gate" Engineering skill references dev's definition-of-done requires it, ops deploy without it. · p=Without strategy, testing whatever agent felt like writing heavy it's easy, absent it's needed, slow fast. pyramid keeps feedback fast (most tests cheap low), floors keep coverage honest, gate matrix makes "tested enough ship" lookup, negotiation. · wu=Triggers: "test strategy," "what tests need," "coverage floor," "release gate," "can ship," "gate check," "is pyramid healthy," required tier-check inside dev's code-review step definition-of-done. · st:/ Protocol=`A change arrives at the gate \· -> Classify: change type (feature / fix / refactor / config / data-adjacent / security-adjacent) \· -> Look up required tiers in assets/release-gate-matrix.md \· -> Verify: required tiers exist, run green, assert behavior (not just execute) \· + coverage ≥ floors (config) for touched code` · in=**Keep pyramid.** Default shape: ~70% unit ~20% integration ~10% end-to-end (marketplace-sourced default, config-overridable business). inverted pyramid E2E-heavy, unit-light slow, flaky, finding itself. **Tests F.I.R.S.T.** Fast, Independent, Repeatable, Self-validating, Timely (credit: agentic-qe). test needs babysitting, ordering, human eyeball output doesn't count toward any tier. **Floors floors.** Coverage floors come config (`coverage_floors`, per-tier, `<FILL_IN>` until operator sets them rule 0.5: quinn invent thresholds). Below-floor coverage touched code GATE FAIL, exceptions gate; operator change floor, quinn can't. **Gate lookup.** Classify change, read matrix, verify listed tiers. matrix dev+quinn co-owned law (changes ADRs); arguing matrix gate time routed dev, absorbed. **Flaky tests quarantined, never deleted.** flaky test moved quarantine (tracked regression-map's flaky register, owner date), coverage hole counts against floor visible pain, gets fixed. Deleting weakening test pass gate review-integrity block (dev's checklist §0) gate FAIL. **Assert behavior.** Spot-check gating tests contain real assertions outcomes suite runs green because asserts nothing GATE FAIL specific empty tests named. · of=`## Gate Check: [change] — type: [classification] \· Required tiers (matrix): [list] \· Present+green: [✓/✗ per tier] \· Coverage on touched code: [n% vs floor] \· Fragile areas touched: [none / list → targeted suites ✓/✗] \· Flaky quarantine impact: [none / holes counted] \· ` · pr=**The gate lookup, negotiation** matrix changes ADRs, gate-time arguments., **Pyramid shape: tests cheap low** inverted pyramids findings., **Floors operator-set; quinn enforces, never invents waives them** (rule 0.5)., **Flaky quarantined counted, never deleted** invisible coverage holes things break., **Green means asserted** test checks nothing proves nothing., **A gate verdict evidence-backed** tier runs coverage numbers attached, rule-0.6 flag. · f=coverage floors configured gate tier presence green assertions only; state loudly floors unset recommend values operator (labeled reasoning-based)., test infrastructure (new business) minimum viable gate: unit tests non-trivial logic one E2E happy path critical flow, labeled provisional; propose full matrix operator., Change type ambiguous gate stricter classification; ambiguity resolved dev, choosing easier row., Emergency hotfix pressure matrix's hotfix row applies (reduced pre-ship tiers, mandatory post-ship completion within set window, logged debt) never silent skip. · b:with Other Skills=**dev/code-review-standards** checks tests exist per-PR (step 3); owns release-level gate strategy checks reference., **regression-map** (sibling) adds targeted-suite requirement fragile areas; gate enforces it., **browser-verification** (sibling) supplies E2E tier's browser evidence (Playwright) decides it's required., **ops** ships GATE PASS owns rollback; pass necessary, sufficient., **charter-enforcement** (sibling) block shipping change independently test results security gate quality gate separate verdicts. · h2:Stack Notes (dated)=`assets/stack-notes-rust-testing-2026-07.md` Rust test mechanics mapped pyramid tiers. Applies stack-profile names Rust; adopted marketplace (ECC) 2026-07-10; method conflicts resolve skill.